g" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"207" class=3D"mw-file-element=
" data-file-width=3D"953" data-file-height=3D"789"></a><figcaption>A space-=
filling tetrahedral disphenoid inside a cube. Two edges have <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dihedral_angle" title=3D"Dihedral angle">dihedra=
l angles</a> of 90=C2=B0, and four edges have dihedral angles of 60=C2=B0.<=
/figcaption></figure>
<p>A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disphenoid" title=3D"Dispheno=
id">disphenoid</a> is a tetrahedron with four congruent triangles as faces;=
 the triangles necessarily have all angles acute.  The regular tetrahedron =
is a special case of a disphenoid. Other names for the same shape include b=
isphenoid, isosceles tetrahedron and equifacial tetrahedron.
</p>
<div style=3D"clear:both;" class=3D""></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Orthoschemes">Orthoschemes<=
