div>
<p>Denote the circumradius of a tetrahedron as <i>R</i>.  Let <i>a</i>, <i>=
b</i>, <i>c</i> be the lengths of the three edges that meet at a vertex, an=
d <i>A</i>, <i>B</i>, <i>C</i> the length of the opposite edges.  Let <i>V<=
/i> be the volume of the tetrahedron.  Then<sup id=3D"cite_ref-32" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetrahedron#cite_note-=
32"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-33" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetrahedron#cite_note-33"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e R=3D{\frac {\sqrt {(aA+bB+cC)(aA+bB-cC)(aA-bB+cC)(-aA+bB+cC)}}{24V}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <msqrt>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>a</mi>
              <mi>A</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>b</mi>
              <mi>B</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>c</mi>
              <mi>C</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>a</mi>
              <mi>A</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>b</mi>
              <mi>B</mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
